  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "> \ud83e\udd16 This PR was written by Coder Agent on behalf of Jake Howell\n\nCloses https://github.com/coder/internal/issues/1373\n\nThe `updateActiveTemplateVersion` mutation awaits `queryClient.invalidateQueries` in its `onSuccess` callback, which refetches the template-by-name query. With `mockResolvedValueOnce` the refetch fell through to the real `API.getTemplateByName` implementation (axios \u2192 MSW), adding non-deterministic latency that pushed `toast.success` past the `waitFor` timeout under CI load.\n\nFix: `mockResolvedValue` (not `Once`) so the refetch resolves instantly via the mock.\n\nVerified with 100/100 consecutive passes.",
